&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB PURPOSE - SUMMARY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;The Account Manager is confident in managing workloads and projects, consistently demonstrating strong strategic thinking and sound judgement. They are trusted by clients to understand issues, agreements, and priorities, and to deliver end to end work seamlessly and reliably. Highly collaborative and approachable, they are valued by both colleagues and clients. A critical strength of the role is the ability to manage client expectations, identify priority projects, and strategically deploy internal resources to ensure timely, high-quality delivery that meets agreed standards.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;KEY RESPONSIBILITIES AND ACCOUNTABILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Understanding the Agency&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Understand and champion Burson&amp;nbsp;Strategies, its values, offering, and ways of working.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Demonstrate a clear understanding of the roles and responsibilities across group agency resources, building effective and profitable relationships while acting as a key intermediary between clients, account teams, and internal departments.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Contribute to the delivery of Agency financial performance goals, maintaining regular dialogue with leadership on account and financial performance.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Creativity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Accurately interpret and articulate client feedback, comments, and actions, confirming alignment in writing to ensure shared understanding.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Lead creative briefings that are clear, concise, insightful, and inspirational.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Actively contribute informed opinions during the creative process to ensure all work remains on-brand and on-brief.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Lead creative presentations to clients (face-to-face where possible), clearly articulating how ideas address strategic objectives, brand guidelines, and briefs.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Serve as a brand guardian, demonstrating a strong command of client tone of voice, brand positioning, and messaging.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Commercial Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Maintain a thorough understanding of Client–Agency contracts across all relevant accounts.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Guide and support the account team on correct financial processes, implementing regular forums to ensure shared understanding of account financials.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Accurately scope and estimate work following the receipt of new briefs, ensuring all projects are delivered within agreed budgets through regular WIP review and re-estimation where scope changes occur.&lt;/div

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
