&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB SUMMARY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Account Managers in Scanad&#39;s PR team are pivotal in both delivering excellent communication outcomes and fostering a stimulating environment for team success. This role requires staying informed beyond just media contacts to ensure maximum impact for our work. Account Managers are responsible for the effective operationalization of client projects and the smooth weekly running of accounts. Proactive and positive management of client relationships is critical for success in this position.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;KEY RESPONSIBILITIES &amp;amp; ACCOUNTABILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Communication &amp;amp; Planning:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Providing strategic counsel to clients and developing comprehensive communication plans.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Developing and executing media relations strategies, including identifying outreach opportunities, drafting media materials, and pitching to media.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Developing messaging and drafting diverse stakeholder communications (e.g., press releases, speeches, presentations).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Developing and executing executive visibility and thought leadership campaigns.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Understanding the role of, developing strategies for, and actively contributing to the development of social, digital, and audio-visual content.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Actively managing partner and client relations for collaborative initiatives like product launches, events, and other programs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Participating in pitch execution, from contributing to strategy and creative development to taking ownership of project management and quality standards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Delivering essential administrative and organizational support to senior colleagues.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Actively contributing to developing high-performing teams that consistently exceed client and agency expectations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Client Management:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Developing a deep understanding of clients’ businesses, communication goals, and strategic plans to achieve those goals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Effectively defining client challenges, agreeing on appropriate communication briefs, and collaborating within the PR&amp;amp;I team and across the agency to deliver effective solutions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working with senior team members to develop overarching strategies and annual plans to meet client objectives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working independently to manage the day-to-day implementation of client activities, both from the office and on-site, including promptly responding to

&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Role Summary&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Content Manager is responsible for overseeing the creation, editing, quality assurance, and publishing of content across digital platforms. The role ensures all content is accurate, engaging, brand-aligned, and optimized for audience engagement while supporting clients&#39; business and communication objectives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Manage content quality and ensure all published content meets editorial and brand standards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Edit and proofread content for clarity, accuracy, consistency, grammar, and style.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Verify facts, statistics, dates, names, and other content details before publication.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Review and approve content before client submission or publication.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Write, edit, and adapt content for websites, social media, and digital campaigns.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Collaborate with Creative, Client Service, and Strategy teams to develop effective content solutions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Work with regional and global teams to ensure consistency in messaging across markets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Manage social media content and community engagement where required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Monitor content performance, audience engagement, and competitor activity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Train, guide, and support copywriters and content contributors.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Manage external content partners and digital agencies where applicable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Role Requirements&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Education&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bachelor&#39;s Degree in Communications, Journalism, Marketing, Public Relations, or a related field.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Experience&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Minimum 5 years&#39; experience in content management, digital marketing, journalism, advertising, or communications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience creating and managing content for digital and social media platforms.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Agency experience is an added advantage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience with CMS platforms such as WordPress is preferred.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Skills &amp;amp; Competencies&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Excellent writing, editing, and proofreading skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Strong understanding of digital content and social media best practices.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Exceptional attention to detail.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Strong communication and presentation skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Creative thinking and storytelling ability.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ability to manage multiple projects in a fast-paced environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Strong stakeholder management and collaboration skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Company Overview&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ogilvy Africa is the continent&#39;s largest agency network, serving over 40 countries through a team of approximately 900 professionals across Central, East, and West Africa.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of the global Ogilvy and WPP network, we partner with leading brands to drive growth through creativity, data, content, and technology. Our integrated One Ogilvy model delivers solutions across Advertising, Branding &amp;amp; Content, Experience, PR &amp;amp; Influence, and Media.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Beliefs at Ogilvy&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;People Need Regular OS Upgrades&lt;/strong&gt; – Continuous learning and gr

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;padding-left: 40px;&quot;&gt;As a Content Writer, you&#39;ll be a key contributor to the written content and creative vision for our in-house agency team. You will play a vital role in developing compelling content for a large portfolio of alco-bev brands in the fast-paced environment of a social media newsroom. You’ll combine your strong creative talent, with a particular emphasis on copywriting and content creation, and an understanding of visual trends with a deep knowledge of social media dynamics, social listening, and in-culture content creation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;padding-left: 40px;&quot;&gt;Reporting to the Creative Director or Associate Creative Director, you’ll be instrumental in ensuring our client&#39;s brands not only stand out but also resonate deeply with target audiences in the ever-evolving digital landscape. This is a mid-to-senior level position for a highly creative and strategic thinker with a solid track record of developing and executing impactful campaigns in the social media space.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Creative Development &amp;amp; Execution&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the development and implementation of innovative creative strategies that align with brand identities and marketing objectives across all social media platforms (TikTok, Instagram, Twitter/X, YouTube, etc.).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop compelling copy and content for various social media formats, including captions, scripts, stories, and social-first articles, ensuring a consistent brand voice and tone.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage provided AI powered tools to enhance efficiency in the creative content output.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with designers and art directors to create visually engaging content, providing direction and feedback to ensure copy and visuals work harmoniously.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In-Culture Content &amp;amp; Storytelling&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Play a key role in the development of content that taps into current trends, memes, hashtags, and cultural moments, with a focus on crafting engaging narratives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Integrate social listening insights into the creative process, ensuring content is relevant, resonant, and drives engagement, with a strong emphasis on impactful storytelling.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the creation of authentic and culturally relevant content that speaks to diverse audiences and fosters brand affinity through powerful and persuasive copy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaboration &amp;amp; Communication&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with strategy analysts, designers, art directors, and content creators, providing clear direction and feedback on copy and content development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with cross-functional teams, including social media managers, strategists, and account managers, to align creative execution with overall campaign goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Present creative concepts and copy ideas effectively to internal teams and stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Brand Voice &amp;amp; Messaging&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure all written communications adhere to brand guidelines and maintain a consistent brand voice and tone across all social media touchpoints.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to elevating the written aesthetic and messaging of our brands, pushing creative boundaries while staying true to brand values and target audience expectations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Uphold the highest standards of creative excellence, ensuring all written content reflects the premium quality of our client&#39;s alco-bev portfolio.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Performance &amp;amp; Optimi

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Designer will create engaging and visually appealing multimedia content across various platforms, including digital and print. This role requires a highly creative individual with strong technical skills in graphic design, video editing, and animation. The Designer will collaborate closely with content managers and other team members to develop high-quality multimedia assets that effectively communicate brand messages and enhance the user experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Visual Design:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Create visually appealing graphics, illustrations, infographics, logos, and other visual elements for digital and print materials, ensuring brand consistency across all design assets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Animation &amp;amp; Video Production:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Conceptualize, script, shoot, and edit videos for various purposes. Create and design digital images, video animations, and textual animations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaboration:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Work closely with content managers and cross-functional teams (program management, community managers, developers) to generate creative ideas and concepts.&lt;/li&gt;
