&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The writer is responsible for developing engaging and persuasive written content for advertising campaigns. They generate original ideas, straplines, slogans, body copy, jingles, and scripts that capture the target audience&#39;s attention and effectively promote client products or brands. Working closely with Art Directors and cross-functional teams, the writer ensures creative alignment and delivers impactful advertising across various media. This role requires a highly creative individual with strong writing skills, a deep understanding of market trends, and the ability to manage projects under tight deadlines.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Creative Content Development: Generate original, clear, and persuasive copy for various advertising formats (e.g., straplines, slogans, body copy, jingles, scripts) to promote client brands. Develop creative ideas and concepts, often in partnership with an Art Director, and update digital media with snappy, timely content.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Market &amp;amp; Brand Understanding: Stay updated on new ideas, techniques, styles, and market trends to inspire creativity. Familiarize with client products, services, target audiences, and competitor activities to inform effective messaging.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaboration &amp;amp; Client Engagement: Liaise with clients to interpret briefs and present creative ideas to colleagues and clients. Work closely within account teams and build key relationships with Art Directors, Account Management, Planning, and Traffic departments to discuss client requirements and core messages.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Quality Assurance &amp;amp; Revision: Meticulously proofread all copy for spelling and grammar. Amends, revise, or redevelop adverts and campaigns in response to feedback from creative directors, account teams, or clients, ensuring creative executions align with strategic concepts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Project &amp;amp; Commercial Management: Manage multiple campaigns simultaneously, often under pressure and to tight deadlines. Oversee campaigns through the production stage to completion, including liaising with external suppliers such as designers, illustrators, photographers, and production companies. Contribute to the financial management of projects, ensuring work is produced on time and within budget, and understand relevant contractual agreements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;padding-left: 40px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education: &lt;/strong&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree or Diploma in Marketing, Communications, English, Journalism, Advertising, or a related field.&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience: &lt;/strong&gt;Proven experience as a Copywriter in an advertising agency or similar creative role.&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Portfolio:&lt;/strong&gt; A strong portfolio showcasing a diverse range of successful advertising copy and campaigns.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional writing, editing, and proofreading skills with strong attention to detail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High level of creativity and ability to generate original, imaginative, and persuasive ideas.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication, presentation, and interpersonal skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong collaboration and teamwork abilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effective time management and project management skills, with the ability to manage multiple projects under tight deadlines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of advertising principles, market trends, client brands, and target audiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to adapt and revise work based on feedback.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic understanding of project budgeting and financial aspects in an agency setting.&lt;br&
